	9974	2013-12-19 20:00:08.470	On page 45 Catherine Ponder writes "Forgiveness Is The Answer"  She says the word forgiveness means "give for" ---to let go of old ideas, feelings or conditions and to give (yourself) something better in their place. 

In other words release not regret - release not remorse - release not anger - release not hatred. Now how do you do this?  There is a problem person for me at work. There are people who took action against me in the past that were very difficult to deflect. There are tons of things that I have said or done that I would not do or say today. So I have "baggage" How do you get rid of the baggage? 

By prayer, by faith , by letting go and let God and affirmations. When you find yourself clinging to the thought of a troublesome situation, Catherine Ponder writes " Declare to the situation or personalities involved: I RELEASE AND LET GO AND LET GOD.  Through release, your power for attracting good is greatly increased"  She also reminds us to be sure we release and let go of any and all attachments.

 

excerpt found here.  

http://mystic.istandforgod.com/forgiveness.html

	10021	2014-01-29 10:09:23.000	http://english.stackexchange.com/questions/132423/word-or-phrase-for-the-beginning-or-end-of-an-event-or-period-of-time
Terminus (plural termini, if you want to be stuffy) is the Latin word for either end of a 1-dimensional extent, and specifically of motion along that dimension. If one uses a Time Is Linear Motion metaphor theme, and considers the timeline of an event, one can talk about the beginning as the terminus a quo 'the terminus from which', and the ending as the terminus ad quem 'the terminus toward which'. These are all established words and phrases in English. -  John Lawler Oct 21 '13 at 17:04 		1000

	5455	2012-08-21 19:32:32.453	Paul was Jewish but NOT a "Christian"
August 21, 2012 By Kurt Willems 0 Comments and 0 Reactions
WP Greet Box icon
X
Hello fellow Twitter user! Don't forget to Twit this post if you like it, or follow me on Twitter if you find me interesting.
An excellent discussion on Jesus Creed:

"Mark Nanos is on a mission to expound for readers of Paul a Paul who never broke from Judaism. His project, and here we are sketching some of what he says in the book edited by Mike Bird called The Apostle Paul, is both about rhetoric and theology. Nanos, who plays golf well and is a Jewish scholar of Paul, has been stumping for his themes for more than a decade. The rhetoric is clear: Christians have explained their faith, in particular the theology of Paul, at the expense of Judaism.

.The theology of Paul, then, needs another explanation. If the traditional view made Jews legalists, the new perspective (Nanos argues) makes Jews ethnocentric. He wants to argue neither of these categories belong on the table.

Paul never left Judaism and the only difference between Paul and other forms of Judaism is that Paul's Judaism had Jesus as the Messiah. Paul was Torah-observant, never left being Torah-observant [I'd quote Acts 23:6 here, but he doesn't; there Paul says "I am a Pharisee"], and Paul's mission was to expand the Shema faith of Judaism - One God - to include Gentiles. So, Paul's mission was including Gentiles into one Judaism. Freedom from the Torah is only for non-Jewish Christians; Jewish Christians remained under the Torah. Schreiner's response focuses on Paul no longer being Torah observant, and he points to Peter in Galatians 2:11-14 (eating with Gentiles) and Paul saying in Romans 14:20 that all foods were clean.

It is big, then, for Nanos to say a major cutting edge between Paul and other forms of Judaism was that Paul permitted Gentile "conversion" without becoming "proselytes" to Judaism. You could convert to Judaism but did not have to become a Jew by undergoing circumcision. Paul opposes proselyte circumcision for Gentile "converts" to Judaism, because circumcision entails Torah observance, and Gentiles don't have to obey the whole Torah.

Nanos, then, has a narrowed meaning for "works of the law": it's about circumcision. Works of the law ultimately leads to changed ethnicity or to ethnic Jewishness." (Read full article here)

*   Customer Services *ClearLogicGroup Inc. * Best way to CALL Me today: * 510-747-8583 *   * Support@ClearLogicGroup.com  * Toll Free: 1-800-270-0153 *

	5552	2012-10-18 21:42:27.493	At our Clean Slate clinic you can get a legal consultation with an advocate to discuss any criminal record remedies available to you.  In order to have a consultation you will need to obtain a copy of your criminal history.  You can get this information from either the Alameda County Sheriff's Department or the California State Department of Justice.  Below is information on how to get a copy of your record.  Once you get the record, then you can drop-in at one of our Clean Slate Clinic locations (no appointment necessary).

ALAMEDA COUNTY RAP SHEETS

Get a copy of your Alameda County RAP sheet ONLY if you know you do not have any arrests or convictions outside of Alameda County.  You may obtain a copy of your Alameda RAP sheet by going in person to:

Alameda County Sheriff's Department
15001 Foothill Boulevard
San Leandro, CA 94578
Phone: (510) 667-3190

The hours are 8:30 am to 3:30 pm.  The cost is $25, cash only.  You must appear in person as you will be fingerprinted.  The process takes about one hour.  Clear any outstanding warrants before appearing.

CALIFORNIA RAP SHEETS
For a RAP sheet that reports all of your arrests and convictions in every county in California, you must obtain a RAP sheet from the California Department of Justice.  Call the East Bay Community Law Center (510-548-4040) and ask for a DOJ rap sheet information packet.  You can also visit the DOJ website at http://ag.ca.gov/fingerprints/security.php

Hayward Clinic
Mondays, 10 am - 1 pm
Eden Area One-Stop Career Center
24100 Amador Street, 3rd Floor

Oakland Clinic
Tuesdays, 10 am - 1 pm
Alameda County Law Library

	6639	2013-01-01 17:41:58.930	

Dear Mr Adeniji

 

Complaint regarding Adeniji and Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited

 

We refer to your complaint received on 2 January, 2013 about Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited.

 

It appears that Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited has not had an opportunity to resolve your complaint through their Internal Dispute Resolution ("IDR") process.

 

Under the Rules of the Credit Ombudsman Service Limited ("COSL"), Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited must first be given the opportunity to address the issues raised in your complaint through their IDR process before COSL can consider your complaint.

 

Next Step

 

Before we can investigate your complaint, you will need to raise your complaint with Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited's Complaint Contact Person in the first instance.  While our Rules do not require you to raise your complaint with Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited in writing, we suggest that you:

 

    write to Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited's Complaints Contact Person (see below) outlining your complaint;
    advise Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited's Complaints Contact Person that COSL has referred you to them and quote your COSL Case Number (13/0002); and
    indicate in your letter that you are making a complaint (not an enquiry) and ask that your complaint be referred to Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited's Internal Dispute Resolution process.

 

Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited's Complaints Contact Person's details:

 

N       Aussie Complaints Officer

T        (02) 8297 0488

E        customerdisputeresolution@aussie.com.au

F        (02) 8297 0192

 

Under the COSL Rules, Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited is required to provide you with a response to your complaint as soon as possible, but within 45 days of your complaint being made (or within 21 days if the complaint is in relation to an application for a financial hardship arrangement).

 

Contacting COSL again

 

If you are not satisfied with Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited's response, or if Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited has not provided a response within 45 days of your complaint being made (or within 21 days if the complaint is in relation to an application for a financial hardship arrangement), please let us know and we will resume assessing your complaint.

 

If Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited has provided you with a response, please provide us with:

 

1.      a copy of their response (if the response is in writing) or a description of their response (if the response is not in writing); and

2.      the reasons why you think your complaint or some parts of your complaint remains unresolved.

 

Further Information

We have sent a letter to Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited to advise them that:

 

1. they must not initiate enforcement action;

 

2. where enforcement action has already commenced, they must not continue the enforcement action and, in particular, they must not:

 

(i)    seek judgment in the legal proceedings; or

 

(ii)   where default judgment has been entered, seek to enforce the default judgment;

 

3. they must not sell the debt or assign any right to recover the debt; and

 

4. if they have not already done so, they must not list a default on your credit reference file.

 

	

If your complaint is about a loan, please note that interest, fees and charges continue to accrue on your loan while we are considering your complaint. You should therefore continue meeting your payment obligations under the loan.  If you are requesting a payment variation on grounds of financial hardship, you should try to make such payments as you are reasonably able to while we are considering your request.
 
 

 

 

 

 

 

 

To view a copy of our Rules, familiarise yourself with our procedures or find out more about the Credit Ombudsman Service, please visit www.cosl.com.au.

 

Please contact Candice Chung on 02 9273 8486 or by email at candice.chung@cosl.com.au if you wish to discuss this case further.

 

 

Sincerely

 

 

 

Daphne Sete

Administrator

One of the best opportunities proved to be Spain, starting with the Muslim conquest of 711. Indeed, things were so good for Jews there, that to this day, half the Jewish world is known as Sephardi meaning "Spanish." (The other half would later become known as Ashkenazi, meaning "German.") (1)

In the Muslim Spain, Jews found a symbiotic relationship emerging between them and the non-Jewish world that surrounded them.

So for one thing, the Muslims impacted on the Jews. Some of the greatest Jewish scholars wrote in Arabic. But the impact was much greater the other way around. Indeed there can be no question that the Islamic world, especially in Spain, did remarkably well because of the large number of Jews who were allowed to operate freely there. 	4803	2010-12-02 17:30:00.000	An ambassador for Qatar's bid to stage the 2022 FIFA World CupT, former France midfielder Zinedine Zidane was all smiles on a dramatic Thursday afternoon in Zurich.

Speaking exclusively to FIFA.com, the usually reserved Zizou voiced his delight at the Qataris' successful candidature and outlined what it means to him on a personal level and to the Arab world as a whole.

FIFA.com: Zinedine, how do you feel about the announcement?
Zinedine Zidane: Relieved more than anything because it's never easy to support a bid. It's like a competition. What makes me happy is the fact that the message I was trying to convey throughout the campaign seems to have got through. I was saying that football belonged to the whole world, and now Russia and Qatar, who've never organised the World Cup, will finally be hosting this amazing event. There's a certain logic in that decision and it's fantastic news for both countries.

You seem very happy. Why is that exactly?
I'm proud to have been part of this bid, which I've supported all the way through. I'm proud to have made my contribution to a new country getting the World Cup. Qatar and the entire Middle East as a whole deserves this event and that makes me happy.

You mention the Middle East. Do you see this as something that resonates beyond Qatar?
Yes, it's a victory for the Arab world. Qatar has received support from the Arab world as a whole and I think that's been an important factor. Now they've got a little bit of time to get down to work and do what they have to do, which is to harness sport and football to achieve some big things. They've got ten years to put a team together and stage a wonderful World Cup.

What do you think tilted the balance in Qatar's favour?
I think it was the fact they'd be new hosts that made the difference. When he made the announcement President Blatter seemed delighted that FIFA and its Executive Committee were happy to entrust the tournament to a country that had never hosted it before. That's what stood out for me. And as far as I'm concerned, it's a logical choice. But obviously, when it comes it down to the voting, it's the little details that make the difference.

You went through a similar experience when France was awarded the 1998 FIFA World Cup. Can you remember how you felt then?
It came as a bit of a shock to me. It must have been before 1994 and I was just making my way into the France team. I clearly remember saying to myself that if France got the tournament, I'd be in with a chance of playing in it, of being part of it. It was great for France, but for me personally it was even more amazing to think that I could take part in it as a member of the national team.

So what was it actually like to take part?
Well, you know, you can't ask for anything more than to play in the World Cup at home and to beat Brazil 3-0 to win it. There's no doubt about that! (laughs)

This is only the start for Qatar. Will you have a role to play in the years to come?
I don't have any exact role right now. My job was to support the bid, and I've done that. I'm happy with my contribution and we'll just have to wait and see what happens in the future. What's important right now is to savour the moment and I'm delighted to have played my part in a winning team.		805

	4807	2010-12-05 21:47:10.000	WikiLeaks Uses Swiss Web Address as Options Narrow.

Assange relies on Swiss Web address, financial accounts as WikiLeaks dodges online threats
The Associated Press
Post a Comment
By JOHN HEILPRIN Associated Press
GENEVA December 6, 2010 (AP)

WikiLeaks' elusive founder, his options dwindling, has turned to Switzerland's credit, postal and Internet infrastructure to keep his online trove of U.S. State Department cables afloat.

Supporters say Julian Assange, an Australian living in Britain, is considering seeking asylum in Switzerland. He told a Spanish newspaper that he faced "hundreds of death threats," including some targeting his lawyers and children, aside from the pressure he is getting from prosecutors in the U.S. and other countries.

After a number of web companies dropped WikiLeaks, much of the site's traffic was coming through the wikileaks.ch Web address Sunday. The address is controlled by the Swiss Pirate Party, a group that formed two years ago to campaign for freedom of information. The site's main server in France went offline but it remained reachable through a Swedish server.

The site showed Assange had begun seeking donations to an account under his name through the Swiss postal system in Bern, the Swiss capital, while also using a Swiss-Icelandic credit card processing center and other accounts in Iceland and Germany. He lost a major source of revenue when the online payment service provider PayPal cut off the WikiLeaks account over the weekend.

Assange has been widely praised and criticized. Supporters view him as a savior of the media and free speech; critics vilify him for brazenly unleashing diplomatic secrets, as well as for earlier leaks involving the wars in Iraq and Afghanistan.

U.S. Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell called Assange "a high-tech terrorist." He told NBC's "Meet the Press" he hopes Assange will be prosecuted for the "enormous damage" the disclosures have done to the country and to its relationship with its allies.

But even as governments put pressure on Assange, WikiLeaks lives on. The Swiss Pirate Party said Sunday that wikileaks.ch was receiving about 3,000 visitors a second.

The party also said supporters are creating "mirrors" of the WikiLeaks site on their own servers, meaning the diplomatic cables will remain available even if WikiLeaks loses its own site.

"Even if you take down the server in Sweden, it's too late," Swiss Pirate Party Vice President Pascal Gloor told The Associated Press on Sunday.

"There are hundreds of mirrors of WikiLeaks now," he said. "It's a test for Internet censorship. Can governments take something off the Net? I think not. There are copies of the website everywhere."

PayPal, a subsidiary of U.S.-based online marketplace operator eBay Inc., said it cut off the WikiLeaks website because it was engaged in illegal activity.

Assange is now in Britain, according to his British lawyer. Marc Andrey, a spokesman for the financial services arm of Swiss Post, told the Swiss weekly NZZ am Sonntag that Assange stated when opening an account with the postal system that he had a residence in Geneva.

Andrey said the Swiss Post was reviewing its "relationship" with Assange. He would have to prove he obtained Swiss residency, lives near the Swiss border, or owns property or does business in Switzerland to keep the Postfinance bank account that he opened last month.

The U.S. ambassador to Switzerland, Donald Beyer, told NZZ am Sonntag that Switzerland "should very carefully consider whether to provide shelter to someone who is on the run from the law." The SonntagsZeitung quoted Beyer as saying he told the Swiss government that WikiLeaks would likely post more than 250 cables from the American Embassy in Bern.

The Swiss Web address wikileaks.ch became the site's main access point on Friday after EveryDNS, based in Manchester, New Hampshire, stopped accepting traffic to the site's principal address - wikileaks.org - saying cyber attacks threatened the rest of its network.

Amazon previously stopped hosting WikiLeaks' Web site and governments and hackers were continuing to go after the organization.

	4808	2010-12-05 22:19:16.307	WikiLeaks Uses Swiss Web Address as Options Narrow. Assange relies on Swiss Web address, financial accounts as WikiLeaks dodges online threats The Associated Press Post a Comment By JOHN HEILPRIN Associated Press GENEVA December 6, 2010 (AP). Pages 3-4.

French web hosting company OVH, which owns a server wikileaks.ch had been using, didn't immediately respond to calls Sunday. France's Industry Minister Eric Besson had warned Friday that it was unacceptable to host a site that "violates the secret of diplomatic relations."

The Swiss Pirate Party convened an impromptu news conference late Friday in a high-tech media building in Biel, Switzerland. Its leaders said they had no special knowledge of Assange's whereabouts or ability to contact him, but had spoken with him weeks ago to help seek asylum in Switzerland. That was during Assange's visit to Geneva last month when he spoke to reporters at the United Nations.

In an online chat with El Pais in Spain, Assange said the hunt for him was tough.

"We have hundreds of specific death threats from U.S. military militants. That is not unusual, and we have become practiced from past experiences at ignoring such threats from Islamic extremists, African kleptocrats and so on," he said.

"Recently the situation has changed with these threats now extending out to our lawyers and my children," he added. "However, it is the specific calls from the elites of U.S. society for our assassination, kidnapping and execution that is more concerning."

Assange is wanted in Sweden to face allegations of sexual offenses against two women, charges he denies, but the United States nor any other country has lodged any charges against him over the leaked documents.

Australia would give consular help to Assange if he is arrested abroad and he is entitled to return home as well, Australian Attorney General Robert McClelland said Monday. But he also condemned the leaks as harming security and said Australia is obligated to help the criminal investigation of Assange's activities.

"Free speech is one thing, we all respect that, but we also respect the freedoms and the rights of people to live without fear," McClelland told reporters.

	5063	2011-09-03 12:49:14.780	Hey -

Stanford is offering a free online course in Artificial Intelligence starting in October.

Registration has started and its an (optional) full course work with homework, lectures, official statement of accomplishment etc

You can signup for the course here:

http://www.ai-class.com/  or directly here :  https://www.ai-class.com/registration/

The course description is here:

http://robots.stanford.edu/cs221/
Overview

    CS221 is the introductory course into the field of Artificial Intelligence at Stanford University. It covers basic elements of AI, such as knowledge representation, inference, machine learning, planning and game playing, information retrieval, and computer vision and robotics. CS221 is a broad course aimed to teach students the very basics of modern AI. It is prerequisite to many other, more specialized AI classes at Stanford University. 

Instructors

    Peter Novig and Sebastian Thrun took over CS221 from Professor Andrew Y. Ng in 2010. Dr. Peter Norvig is author of the celebrated textbook Artificial Intelligence: A Modern Approach. He is also Director of Research at Google. Dr. Thrun is well known for his work on robotics and self-driving cars (His team won the DARPA Grand Challenge). Thrun is research professor at Stanford and a Google Fellow. He is one of the youngest individuals ever elected into the National Academy of Engineering (at age 39). 

Who Should Attend?

    With an in-class enrollment of nearly 200 students, CS221 is one of the largest courses taught at Stanford University, across all departments and all disciplines. It is included in the core curriculum of several degree programs at Stanford. The course is tailored towards advanced undergraduate or early graduate students, new to Artificial Intelligence, who wish to learn about the excitement in the field. The course indtroduce a wealth of topics in AI, many of which are then subject of more specialized follow-on classes at Stanford.

    A course with the same title Introduction to Artificial Intelligence will be offered online and free of charge, as an experimantal new course. Using advanced new technology, the instuctors aspire to cover the same materials, and apply the same level of testing. However, to receive Stanford credit, the course has to be taken through Stanford; and students have to be registered at Stanford University. Online students who pass the online class will receive a statement of acknowledgementc in the name of the instructors, but no official Stanford certificate. 

Course Description

    This course is 10 weeks long. The in-class class starts Tue, Sept 27. CS221 consists of

        Approximately 20 lectures. Each lecture includes quizzes that we ask you to do, but which are not counted towards the final grade of this class. Instead, you can see the right answer to each quizz right after submitting your answers.
        Approximately 8 homework assignments. Those are just like our quizzes, and if you do well in the quizzes, you should do well in the assignments. However, we won't show you the correct answer only with a few days delay, to discourage cheating.
        One midterm and one final exam. These are like extended quizzes, covering all subject areas of the course discussed so far. The exams will also check your general knowledge about topics covered in the reading materials (the book). 

    The central objective is to teach basic methods in AI, and to convey enthusiasm for the field. AI has emerged as one of the most impactful disciplines in science and technology. Google, for example, is massively run on AI. Students passing this course should be proficient basic methods of AI, and have a broad overview of the field. 

Passing Requirements

    To pass this course, you have to attend (or watch online) all lectures. You have to turn in all homework assignments and exams. We grant a total of six "late days" which can be used to turn an assignment or an exam in late.

    Stanford has a strong Honor Code. We expect you to honor this code. Violations may lead to disciplinary action against you. 

Prerequisites

    A solid understanding of probability and linear algebra will be required. 		1244

To Contact Us

required Indicates Required Fields
From:

    Email Address - is required when the Request Email Copy is "Yes"
    Confirm Email Address - is required when Email Address is provided

    First Name:
    Middle Initial:
    Last Name:
    Address:
     
    City:
    State:
    Zip Code: -
    Email Address:
    Confirm Email Address:
    Phone Number: () (Numbers only, no dashes)

Business Information (Complaint Against):

    Company Name:
    Company Address:
     
    Company City:
    Company State:
    Company Zip Code: -
    Company Phone Number: () (Numbers only, no dashes)

Comments:

Please include the following information in the text of your complaint if relevant:

    If you have a foreign (non-US) address.
    If you are shareholder, member, or limited partner.
    Name of the product or service involved.
    The dollar amount in dispute.
    The date of the transaction.
    Was the product or service advertised? If so, indicate where and on what date?
    Was a contract signed?
    Identify your attempts to resolve the issue(s) with the company, corporation, or organization.
    Have you contacted another agency for assistance? If so, what agency?
    Have you contacted an attorney? If so, what is the attorney's name, address, and phone number?

Thank you for your internet enquiry

 

Please be advised that foreign currency transfers are NOT permitted on your home loan. One of two things will now happen -

 

1.      The funds might be returned to where they were sent from. This process may take up to 7-10 business days.

 

2.      The receiving party (Westpac) may decide not to return the funds pending the sender making a claim for these funds that could not be allocated. In this event you need to initiate a trace on the transaction via Citibank. Traces of misplaced funds can only be actioned from the originating source.

 

You were advised that Aussie does not offer swift transfer services when you called our contact centre on 27 December

 

To make an electronic deposit to your loan using a foreign currency you need to transfer that foreign currency to your nominated direct debit bank account (Commonwealth Bank) , have those funds converted to Australian dollars and then either transfer those Australian dollars from your Commonwealth Bank netbank service to the Aussie loan or instruct Aussie to take a one time lump sum payment from that Commonwealth account.

 

If you have any further enquiries in this matter please call Aussie on 131333 or 61 2 82970000 from overseas.

Perceptions of Jews by
Renowned Gentiles.


" Some people like the Jews, and some do not. But no thoughtful man can deny the fact that they are, beyond any question, the most formidable and the most remarkable race which has appeared in the world."


-- Winston Churchill



"The Jew is that sacred being who has brought down from heaven the everlasting fire, and has illumined with it the entire world. He is the religious source, spring, and fountain out of which all the rest of the peoples have drawn their beliefs and their religions."


-- Leo Tolstoy



"It was in vain that we locked them up for several hundred years behind the walls of the Ghetto. No sooner were their prison gates unbarred than they easily caught up with us, even on those paths which we opened up without their aid."


-- A. A. Leroy Beaulieu, French publicist, 1842



"The Jew gave us the Outside and the Inside - our outlook and our inner life. We can hardly get up in the morning or cross the street without being Jewish. We dream Jewish dreams and hope Jewish hopes. Most of our best words, in fact - new, adventure, surprise, unique, individual, person, vocation, time, history, future, freedom, progress, spirit, faith, hope, justice - are the gifts of the Jews."


-- Thomas Cahill, Irish Author



"One of the gifts of the Jewish culture to Christianity is that it has taught Christians to think like Jews, and any modern man who has not learned to think as though he were a Jew can hardly be said to have learned to think at all."


-- William Rees-Mogg, former Editor-in-Chief for The Times of London and a member of the House of Lords



"It is certain that in certain parts of the world we can see a peculiar people, separated from the other peoples of the world and this is called the Jewish people.... This people is not only of remarkable antiquity but has also lasted for a singular long time... For whereas the people of Greece and Italy, of Sparta, Athens and Rome and others who came so much later have perished so long ago, these still exist, despite the efforts of so many powerful kings who have tried a hundred times to wipe them out, as their historians testify, and as can easily be judged by the natural order of things over such a long spell of years. They have always been preserved, however, and their preservation was foretold.. My encounter with this people amazes me..."


-- Blaise Pascal, French Mathematician



"The Jewish vision became the prototype for many similar grand designs for humanity, both divine and man made The Jews, therefore, stand at the center of the perennial attempt to give human life the dignity of a purpose."


--Paul Johnson, American Historian



"As long as the world lasts, all who want to make progress in righteousness will come to Israel for inspiration as to the people who had the sense for righteousness most glowing and strongest."


!


--Matthew Arnold, British poet and critic



"Indeed it is difficult for all other nations of the world to live in the presence of the Jews. It is irritating and most uncomfortable. The Jews embarrass the world as they have done things which are beyond the imaginable. They have become moral strangers since the day their forefather, Abraham, introduced the world to high ethical standards and to the fear of Heaven. They brought the world the Ten Commandments, which many nations prefer to defy. They violated the rules of history by staying alive, totally at odds with common sense and historical evidence. They outlived all their former enemies, including vast empires such as the Romans and the Greeks. They angered the world with their return to their homeland after 2000 years of exile and after the murder of six million of their brothers and sisters.

	4057	2008-04-21 11:28:27.760	Thank you for your internet enquiry.

 

In regards to your enquiry about fixing your loan I enclose the following details;

 

 

FIXING A LOAN -

 

INDICATIVE fixed interest rates for standard loan products as at  17.3.2008 are as follows -

 

1 Year - 8.94%

2 Years - 8.79%

3 Years - 8.74%

4 Years - 8.74%

5 Years - 8.69%

 

Higher fixed rates apply to No or Low Doc products, please call 131333 for assistance

 

 

 

The following conditions apply only to the fixed side of a split loan or if the total balance of a loan is fixed. Normal loan conditions will always apply to the side of any split loan that remains on the variable interest rate. It is imperative that you read and understand the following restrictions before entering into an agreement with Aussie to fix your loan.

 

 

* There is no fee to fix a loan.

 

* If there is more than one borrower on the loan then all borrowers MUST BE AWARE of the intention of one borrower to fix a loan. At the time you call Aussie to fix your loan you will be asked the question "Are all co-borrowers aware of your intention to fix today". If you answer no (note this call will be recorded) then the rep will not allow you to fix the loan.

 

* No Redraw is allowed during entire term on a fixed loan or fixed side of a split loan. Any pending redraws must be finalised before the fix is to take place therefore do not apply to fix your loan whilst you still have a redraw pending.

 

 

* Extra repayments are allowed up to 5% of amount fixed per annum. This is calculated by working out 5% of the total amount to be fixed and then dividing this amount by 12 (if on monthly repayments) or by 26 (if on fortnightly repayments). This is the MAXIMUM amount per year extra you are allowed to pay to the fixed loan and does NOT accumulate from year to year. Paying any more than this allowance will incur break costs. If the 5% allowance is paid in lump sums then these lump sums must be made via cheque or money order. They CANNOT be taken via Direct Debit.

 

* The fixed interest rate quoted on application day is indicative and you will not be guaranteed that rate if you wish to proceed. It takes Aussie up to two business days to action your request, if our fixed rates change in that period we will contact you to seek further instructions

 

 

* BREAK COSTS - These costs will be applied if the loan needs to be discharged or the property sold or if the customer wants to break the contract during the fixed term period. Break costs could be very substantial and may run into the thousands of dollars depending on the amount of the fixed loan and the time remaining on the fixed term. The cost is NOT a fee charged by Aussie but should be looked at as a way of compensating our funder back for lost revenue on their investment. Because of this fact break costs will NOT be waived or discounted under any circumstances.

 

 

I hope you have found this information useful and would recommend that you may wish to seek financial advice before making the commitment to fix your loan.

 

If you wish to proceed to fix all or part of your loan you must now TELEPHONE Aussie on 131333 (overseas customers call +612 82970000) where a service rep will RECORD your call and explain the above terms and conditions to you as a "verbal contract".

 

Regards,

 

Stephen Blomfield

	4143	2008-09-25 12:38:39.493	Hey,     Dhalia wants me to write a Reference letter for her for her application to study  for Masters in Nursing at UCSF School of Nursing. Here is a draft. I want to send a copy to her and have her approval before sending it off to her tomorrow. Let me know what you think, son.     Thanks.     Dad     TO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN     My name is Jim Adeyemo Adeniji (65 years old), co-founder and a director of God's Leading Ladies Worldwide (GLLW), an NGO in Nigeria. I head the "Children Deserve Life" (CDL) segment of the organization. GLLW seeks to give support and empower women of diverse ages, at all levels-including the homeless, the lost, the abused, the abandoned, and the handicapped (financial and/or emotional). I had previously worked in England as a volunteer for seven years in a Women Enrichment Program, organized and run  by a British NGO.     Ms. Sabeh, Dhalia was invited to partner with GLLW by one of our directors when they met at a conference on "Support for Abused Teenagers" held in Lagos, Nigeria in 2002.  Dhalia brought to GLLW her knowledge, training, experience, and deep passion for challenged youths. Working for GLLW, she quickly became leader of the team (GLLW Army) that scouts for girls who have taken to the streets, offering medical, rehabilitation, partnership into a new way (of life), supervision and follow-up services. Dhalia was unique in this work by never giving up on, and believing that, everybody can be made or helped to be better, given the opportunity and support. Dhalia became to GLLW `the finaliser' in difficult client cases before the organization. When she is not physically present in Nigeria due to her other commitments, she remains a consultant to GLLW and mentor to `her girls' who keep in touch with her.     Ms. Sabeh showed an unusual flair for and execution of the philosophy of the GLLW. She was able to win with surprising ease, the confidence and trust of many of the organisation's converts/clients. Her unique organizational and communicational skills, reliability, tenacity and innate ability to interact, blend and relate with all kinds of people, at all levels, always endeared Dhalia to members of GLLW and more especially, to the ladies (old and new) who she comes into contact with. Today, many of her direct flock have become responsible and productive members of the society. For instance, two of `her girls' now work full-time for GLLW, while some are productive volunteers.  An important legacy of Ms. Sabeh is that she excelled at pulling in substantial donations (and partners/participants) from important and previously unexplored sources to back up the high number of girls she brought in.     Target population of our NGO is helping the psychologically and medically challenged young women in the society to turn their lives around and achieve their full potentials. If Dhalia Sabeh is given the chance to study nursing at your institution to add to her present innate capability, I am enthusiastically hopeful that she will be a re-incarnation of Mother Theresa in today's troubled society. Ms. Sabeh is intelligent, hardworking, tenacious, sincere and trustworthy. She is a team-player and an achiever who leaves a nostalgic happy feeling everywhere she goes. A nursing career will fulfill her potential to offer more comprehensive service to humanity. I recommend her, without any reservation, for a place in this year's body of nursing students at your institution.     I shall be happy to offer follow up information about Ms. Dhalia Sabeh if needed, in your consideration of her application to study for a nursing degree at your institution. 	4563	2010-05-06 14:48:35.000	Please kindly do me a favor, I will like to generate an entity framework executable from the command-line using the C# compiler, csc.

The AdventureWorks files (.edmx, .designer.cs) were generated using Visual Studio.

I don't know how-to include the .edmx file as a resource in the csc build.

Neither do I know, how-to include the AdventureWorksModel files (.ssdl, .csdl, .msl, .ObjectLayer.cs, .Views.cs) generated by EdmGen in an alternate build.

The debugger message is below:

ArgumentException was unhandled.

The specified named connection is either not found in the configuration, not intended to be used with the EntityClient provider, or not valid.


D:\WordEngineering\InformationInTransit\ProcessLogic\EntityFrameworkSampleBuild.bat

EdmGen /mode:FullGeneration /namespace:InformationInTransit.EntityFramework /project:AdventureWorksModel /connectionstring:"Data Source=(local);Initial Catalog=AdventureWorks;Integrated Security=True"
csc /r:System.Data.Entity.dll EntityFrameworkSample.cs ..\EntityFramework\AdventureWorksModel.Designer.cs


D:\WordEngineering\InformationInTransit\ProcessLogic\EntityFrameworkSample.cs

using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using System.Text;

using InformationInTransit.EntityFramework;

namespace InformationInTransit.ProcessLogic
{
    public class EntityFrameworkSample
    {
        public static void Main(string[] argv)
        {
            PersonQuery();
        }

        public static void PersonQuery()
        {
            try
            {
                using (var context = new InformationInTransit.EntityFramework.Entities())
                {
                    var salesPersons = context.SalesPersons;
                    foreach (var salesPerson in salesPersons)
                    {
                        System.Console.WriteLine
                        (
                           "SalesPerson ID: {0}",
                           salesPerson.SalesPersonID
                        );
                    }
                }
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                System.Console.WriteLine(ex.Message);
            }
        }

        public const string ConnectionString = "metadata=res://*/EntityFramework.AdventureWorks.csdl|res://*/EntityFramework.AdventureWorks.ssdl|res://*/EntityFramework.AdventureWorks.msl;provider=System.Data.SqlClient;provider connection string=\"Data Source=(local);Initial Catalog=AdventureWorks;Integrated Security=True\";";
    }
}

	4564	2010-05-08 13:34:31.327	The simplest way to do this is to use msbuild on the command line and build a csproj and/or sln file rather than directly calling the compiler.  That way you can take advantage of the entitydeploy build task which splits an edmx file up into the separate ssdl, csdl and msl files as well as the code which will store those as resource files in your assembly.  This page might provide some relevant help: http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/0k6kkbsd.aspx

 

If you do want to build on your own, you would need to write some code to extract the separate parts of the edmx file into different files (using linq to xml or something like that).  Then you could either change your connection string to refer to the filenames directly and have the files be external (but in the same directory with your executable), or you could have the compiler embed them as resources using the /res commandline option on the compiler: http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/c0tyye07(VS.80).aspx

 

-          Danny		69

This email acknowledges receipt of your Online Consumer Complaint form.  Based upon your correspondence we have opened a case in the OCC's Customer Assistance Group (CAG).  Please make note of the case number listed above, and provide the number on any future correspondence or contact with our office.
 
We are reviewing the information you provided, and will contact the bank requesting a response to your issues.  In most instances, the bank will respond directly to you and copy us in writing.  Once you receive the bank's response, it is very important that you carefully review their summary and actions taken, if any.
 
If the bank has satisfactorily addressed your issues and/or concerns no further action on your part is required.  If however, the bank failed to address your issues and/or concerns or you disagree with their response, please contact the CAG in writing within 30 days of receipt of the bank's letter.  Please include in your reply the specific issues that the bank failed to address or, if applicable, the reasons you disagree with the bank's assessment.  Also, please include any additional documentation that supports your position.  
 
The OCC examines national banks to ensure their safe and sound financial condition and ensures compliance with applicable banking laws, rules and regulations.  The CAG was established to assist customers who have questions or complaints involving national banks.  For additional information on the OCC and CAG please visit our internet site www.helpwithmybank.gov.
 
The CAG offers guidance, and assists consumers in resolving complaints about national banks and their subsidiaries.  The CAG is not a consumer advocacy or bank advocacy group.  The OCC is an administrative agency and we do not have jurisdiction to resolve contractual and factual issues.  We do not have judicial authority and cannot award damages in excess of a bank's error. 
 
While complaint processing times may vary, on average you should receive a written response from CAG within 60 days after we have a complete file.  
 
If you would like to check the status of your case online, please click on the following link: https://appsec.helpwithmybank.gov/olcc_form/checkstatus.aspx or visit www.helpwithmybank.gov and click on the Check Case Status page.
 
Should you have questions, please contact this office at the number listed below.

If the bank has satisfactorily addressed your issues and/or concerns no further action on your part is required. The OCC examines national banks to ensure their safe and sound financial condition and ensures compliance with applicable banking laws, rules and regulations.  The CAG was established to assist customers who have questions or complaints involving national banks.  For additional information on the OCC and CAG please visit our internet site www.helpwithmybank.gov.
 
The CAG offers guidance, and assists consumers in resolving complaints about national banks and their subsidiaries.  The CAG is not a consumer advocacy or bank advocacy group.  The OCC is an administrative agency and we do not have jurisdiction to resolve contractual and factual issues.  We do not have judicial authority and cannot award damages in excess of a bank's error. 
 
While complaint processing times may vary, on average you should receive a written response from CAG within 60 days after we have a complete file.

436	1587	2004-03-16 00:00:00.000	Microsoft free MSDN Events.
 Session #1: Writing Secure Code Threat Defense. In this session for experienced developers, you will learn established best practices for applying security principles throughout the development process. The session will discuss common security threats faced by application developers, such as buffer overruns, cross-site scripting and denial of service attacks, and you will learn effective strategies to defend against those threats. 
 Session #2: Implementing Application Security by Using the .NET Framework. In this session for experienced developers, you will learn how to implement additional security features to secure applications built on the .NET Framework. The session will discuss security features integrated into the .NET Framework and demonstrate the use of both code access security and role-based security to limit vulnerabilities. You will also learn how to use the cryptographic provider support in the .NET Framework to encrypt and sign data. The session will also cover security best practices for Web applications and Web services built using ASP.NET.

	2735	2007-03-13 07:32:25.307	nig.pepper@bt.com
To:
kenadeniji@hotmail.com

Subject:
RE: Issues with the IAM sample (BT SDK)


Hi Ken,

 

It appears your certificate installation has become corrupted.  Following the steps below should resolve this.  Note however  that BT cannot accept responsibility for any adverse effects incurred following the instructions below.  Caution should be exercised installing and removing certificates from your machine's certificate store.

 

1.       Click Start > Run and type "mmc" in the run command box and hit OK.

2.       This will start the MS Management Console.

3.       Select File > Add/Remove Snap-in

4.       Select the Add button at the bottom of the resulting Dialog.

5.       From the list, select "Certificates" and hit OK.

6.       Select the My user account option and hit Finish, then Close, then OK.

7.       You'll then have a tree list showing "Certificates - Current User".

8.       Expand this and select "Trusted Root Certification Authorities" and "Certificates"

9.       Select the certificate issued to BT SDK CA and hit delete.

10.   Now expand this and select "Trusted People" and "Certificates"

11.   Select the certificate issued to BT SDK Server and hit delete.

12.   Close the management console and run the BT SDK Certificate Viewer from the Start menu.

13.   Install the missing certificates as directed and you should be good to go.

 

Let me know if any of this is unclear and i'll see where we can help you out.

Regards, Nigel		1568

	2742	2007-03-14 19:28:38.000	I have been using UML since 1997.

I do not have experience with StrataSoft Applications.

I have doing windows applications for 20 years.
I initially started doing windows applications using visual basic, both I concentrated on PowerBuilder for client-server development.

I have 10 years of Intranet experience.
Intranet is a later technology, and was only available at the advent of the Internet. Intranet solely means Internet restricted to within our network. With Intranet technology we are using browsers and no longer basing our graphical user interface (GUI) development on windows forms. Security provided by active directory for Lightweight directory access protocol (LDAP).

When I commenced my doctorate studies in 1997, I planned to build a mobile intelligent memory (MIM) with software engineering techniques specializing on the unified modeling language (UML) and unified method.
The thesis focused on combining the storage technology found in compact flash memory, with the security facility ingrained in smart cards - mainly Gemplus and Schlumberger.
The MIM product is an external removable gadget that requires PC connection for interchanging data.
The security taxnomy were role-based access control (RBAC) and least priviledge.

Since each of the component, compact flash memory and smart card, is a separate operating unit, we sought the use of object-oriented technology for interfacing the operations of the 2 components.

The foundation of our research were use-cases, class, sequence, collaboration, and state diagrams.

The use-cases were basically simulations of how the actor interact with the MIM product.

The common file scenarios are open, save, save as, delete, move, metrics, and change properties such as file create and last modified date, access rights - read, write, grant, share.

The class diagrams identified the intrinsic capabilities offered by both physical devices - storage and security, but we also feared that we will have to build a device driver to bridge the storage and security units.

With the standardization on the PC/SC we were no longer confined to proprietary smart card access.

Microsoft's smart card sign-on also relieved us of having to integrate the smart card as a viable identity to the personal computer.

The sequence diagram will illustrate in vertical top-to-bottom layout the step-by-step events that will occur in each life cyle.
For example, when an actor request to open a file, the smart card will only likely have to perform the simple and mundane step of approving the user's authority.
However, metrics are customizable grants, usage include write once, lifetime expantancy, and destroy upon consumption.

The collaboration diagram will in side-by-side horizontal style highlight the message passing between the requester and fulfiller.

The state diagrams are assertions on the pre and post-conditions of a begin and commit transaction.

I did not complete the doctorate in UML prior to re-locating from Australia.

However, I have used Rational Rose, Visio, and Together J, professionally.

Visual Studio reverse engineers code as class diagrams, and generates documents presentable in either XML or HTML format.		1574

	3257	2007-04-11 00:00:03.000		The impetus for YearDay came from seeing some European women at Food4Less 39966 Cedar Boulevard Balantine Plaza Newark 94560 CA French Baguettes.
	These European women probably worked hard in setting up the European Community (EC) but unfortunately did not get the honor deserved.
	The first commandment with a promise, the 5th commandment. Honor thy father and mother.
	For any consentual adult, this commandment also entails the people that are older than us.

	The YearDay function returns the day of the year.
	For the 1st day of the year, January 1, this is obviously 1.
	For the last day of the year, December 31, this is always 365 days in a non leap year.

	YearDay was revived on 20070411 which is the 101st day of the year.
	The Workshop in Heaven table was also created on 20070411.
	The first word, Workshop, is a combination of the words work and shop.
	I was reluctant to use the word workshop because of Bavarian Motor Works (BMW).
	The 5th letter is S which appears similar to the digit 5.
	The middle word, in, starts with the 9th digit and ends with the 14th digit. 14 - 9 = 5.
	The last word, heaven, That's the goalpost I am the founder.
	In the word heaven, starting from the East and counting westward, the 5th letter is E, the 5th alphabet.

	The YearDay function was originally implemented as a computed column in the TheWord table.
	Previously the from date was using GETDATE(); therefore, inaccurately assuming the passed date is always the current year.

	Although God blessed Abraham with the land of Israel, He specifically mentions Abraham's land of origin.

	3469	2007-07-02 20:43:49.777	Lithuanian Jews (known in Yiddish and Haredi English as Litvish  (adjective) or Litvaks (noun)) are Ashkenazi Jews with roots in Lita, a region including not only present-day Lithuania but also Latvia , much of Belarus and the northeastern Suwalki region of Poland. "Lita", also known as "Litvakia", [1] is roughly coterminous with the territory of the Grand Duchy of Lithuania. [2][3]

Lita was historically home to a large and influential Jewish community that was almost entirely eliminated during the Holocaust: see History of the Jews in Lithuania. Before World War II there were over 110 synagogues and 10 yeshivas in Vilnius. [4] About 4,000 Jews were counted in Lithuania during the 2005 census.[5] There are still strong communities of Jews of Lithuanian descent around the world, especially in Israel, the United States and South Africa.
 
The characteristically "Lithuanian" approach to Judaism was marked by a concentration on highly intellectual Talmud study.

February 2013 	    	 Logo 	 Australia's Global Community 	    	 Aussies abroad speak out: What issues should australia be talking about this election?   Australian Prime Minister, the Hon Julia Gillard MP, recently announced the Australian Federal Election will be held on 14 September. This long campaign will provide the opportunity for extended debate on policies by all political parties and the Australian community, wherever they live. We asked nine Australians living abroad what issues they think should be front and centre in the upcoming election discussion, and whether their views have changed since moving overseas. Climate change, innovation, productivity, education and foreign policy are high on the list. Read more or join the conversation here.  	      	 Advance Global Australian Awards Dare to Struggle! The adopted mantra of Barry Plews  Barry Plews decided to up sticks and navigate the complexities of the Chinese creative industry over 18 years ago. This year he is bringing the China Shanghai International Arts Festival to Australia with a Chinese New Year's Day concert on 10 February. We talked to Barry about his connection to Australia and which Australian artists are exciting him at the moment. Read more. 	  	 Advance Global Australian Awards Missed Connections: Aussie illustrator Sophie Blackall in new york  Aussies in New York may be familiar with her beautiful, subway-inspired illustration on display in many trains around the city. Aspiring photojournalist, Viktoria Balanzategui caught up with children's book Illustrator, Sophie Blackall, over a cup of coffee to discuss why she moved to the Big Apple, and what it is about the city that inspires her to draw. Read more.                	  	 Advance Global Australian Awards Vale, Adam Griffiths  The Advance global community mourns the loss of one of our most creative and loving souls, Adam Griffiths. Adam died a hero trying to save another mate's life. We honour his positive and abundant energy, curiosity and humbleness. Please read his story here. 	6686	2013-02-17 21:50:29.390	Dear Mr Adeniji

 

Complaint regarding Adeniji and Aussie Home Loans Pty Limited (Aussie)

 

We refer to your complaint dated 2 January 2013 about Aussie.

 

At the time we received your complaint, it appeared that it had not been through Aussie's Internal Dispute Resolution (IDR) procedures.  As such, you were referred to Aussie's complaint contact person whose role is to address your complaint with a view to settling it.

 

We note that we have not received any correspondence from either party as to the progress or outcome of this complaint.

 

Further Action

 

Please advise us if your complaint has been resolved.

 

If your complaint remains unresolved and you wish to continue your complaint with us, please provide us with:

 

1.      a copy of Aussie's response (if any); and

 

2.      the reasons why you think your complaint or some parts of your complaint remains unresolved.

 

If we do not receive a response from you within 14 days of the date of this letter (being on or before 4 March 2013), we will assume that Aussie has resolved the complaint to your satisfaction or that you no longer wish to pursue your complaint.  Your file will then be closed.

 

Please contact me on 02 9273 8486 or by email at candice.chung@cosl.com.au if you wish to discuss this case further.

 

Sincerely

 

 

 

Candice Chung

	4830	2010-12-26 14:44:30.440	Rabbi Reveals Name of the Messiah. Shortly before he died, one of Israel's most prominent rabbis wrote the name of the Messiah on a small note which he requested would remain sealed until now. When the note was opened, it revealed what many have known for centuries: Yehoshua, or Yeshua (Jesus), is the Messiah.  A few months before he died, one of the nation's most prominent rabbis, Yitzhak Kaduri, supposedly wrote the name of the Messiah on a small note which he requested would remain sealed until now. When the note was unsealed, it revealed what many have known for centuries: Yehoshua, or Yeshua (Jesus), is the Messiah.  With the biblical name of Jesus, the Rabbi and kabbalist described the Messiah using six words and hinting that the initial letters form the name of the Messiah. The secret note said:  Concerning the letter abbreviation of the Messiah's name, He will lift the people and prove that his word and law are valid.  This I have signed in the month of mercy, Yitzhak Kaduri  The Hebrew sentence (translated above in bold) with the hidden name of the Messiah reads: Yarim Ha'Am Veyokhiakh Shedvaro Vetorato Omdim  The initials spell the Hebrew name of Jesus, Yehoshua. Yehoshua and Yeshua are effectively the same name, derived from the same Hebrew root of the word "salvation" as documented in Zechariah 6:11 and Ezra 3:2. The same priest writes in Ezra, "Yeshua son of Yozadak" while writing in Zechariah "Yehoshua son of Yohozadak." The priest adds the holy abbreviation of God's name, ho, in the father's name Yozadak and in the name Yeshua.  With one of Israel's most prominent rabbis indicating the name of the Messiah is Yeshua, it is understandable why his last wish was to wait one year after his death before revealing what he wrote.  When the name of Yehoshua appeared in Kaduri's message, ultra-Orthodox Jews from his Nahalat Yitzhak Yeshiva (seminary) in Jerusalem argued that their master did not leave the exact solution for decoding the Messiah's name.  The revelation received scant coverage in the Israeli media. Only the Hebrew websites News First Class (Nfc) and Kaduri.net mentioned the Messiah note, insisting it was authentic. The Hebrew daily Ma'ariv ran a story on the note but described it as a forgery.  Jewish readers responded on the websites' forums with mixed feelings: "So this means Rabbi Kaduri was a Christian?" and "The Christians are dancing and celebrating," were among the comments.  Israel Today spoke to two of Kaduri's followers in Jerusalem who admitted that the note was authentic, but confusing for his followers as well. "We have no idea how the Rabbi got to this name of the Messiah," one of them said.  Yet others completely deny any possibility that the note is authentic. Kaduri's son, Rabbi David Kaduri, said that at the time the note was written (September 2005), his father's physical condition made it impossible for him to write.   KADURI'S PORTRAYAL OF THE MESSIAH  A few months before Kaduri died at the age of 108, he surprised his followers when he told them that he met the Messiah. Kaduri gave a message in his synagogue on Yom Kippur, the Day of Atonement, teaching how to recognize the Messiah. He also mentioned that the Messiah would appear to Israel after Ariel Sharon's death. (The former prime minister is still in a coma after suffering a massive stroke more than a year ago.)  Other rabbis predict the same, including Rabbi Haim Cohen, kabbalist Nir Ben Artzi and the wife of Rabbi Haim Kneiveskzy.  Kaduri's grandson, Rabbi Yosef Kaduri, said his grandfather spoke many times during his last days about the coming of the Messiah and redemption through the Messiah.  His spiritual portrayals of the Messiah-reminiscent of New Testament accounts-were published on the websites Kaduri.net and Nfc:  "It is hard for many good people in society to understand the person of the Messiah. The leadership and order of a Messiah of flesh and blood is hard to accept for many in the nation. As leader, the Messiah will not hold any office, but will be among the people and use the media to communicate. His reign will be pure and without personal or political desire. During his dominion, only righteousness and truth will reign.  "Will all believe in the Messiah right away? No, in the beginning some of us will believe in him and some not. It will be easier for non-religious people to follow the Messiah than for Orthodox people.  "The revelation of the Messiah will be fullled in two stages: First, he will		2833

	4992	2011-05-15 22:26:36.323	DAVID WILKERSON: POWER AND PRAYER - (Print)       "The whole strange adventure got its start one night as I sat in my study reading Life magazine. I merely turned a page, and at first glance it seemed there was nothing to interest me. The page showed a pen drawing of a trial taking place in New York City, 350 miles away from my home in rural Pennsylvania. I'd never been to New York, and I'd never wanted to go, except perhaps to see the Statue of Liberty.      "I started to flip the page over. But as I did, something caught my eye. It was the eyes of a figure in the drawing - a boy. He was one of seven boys on trial for murder. I held the magazine closer to get a better look. The artist had captured a look of bewilderment, hatred and despair in the young boy's features. Suddenly, I began to cry." - David Wilkerson in "How It All Began"  In 1958, David Wilkerson saw a Life magazine picture of seven New York City teenagers charged with murder, and the Holy Spirit moved him to drive the hundreds of miles from his home in Pennsylvania to New York. He had very little idea about what he would do when he got there, but it didn't take long for him to meet angry, violent kids on the streets of the city - kids that God loved. Soon Wilkerson moved permanently to New York City, and he began a ministry to teens that eventually blossomed and planted new tap roots around the world.  Wilkerson soon founded Teen Challenge, a ministry for teenagers that included a Bible-based recovery program for drug abusers. By 1963, Teen Challenge started spreading to other cities. Wilkerson's book The Cross And The Switchblade, about his early years in New York, became a best seller with 15 million copies distributed in over 30 languages.  "The church has failed," Wilkerson said in a 1963 interview with The LA Times. "And young people are tired of its social club image. They wants some real and vital answers to give them courage to resist urban pressures and temptations."  In 1971, Wilkerson founded World Challenge, which "serves as a corporate umbrella for Reverend Wilkerson's crusades, minister conferences, book and tract publishing, video production, street evangelism, literature distribution, feeding programs, drug and alcohol rehabilitation centers and other charitable outreaches." Since reading that Life article in 1958, Wilkerson's ministries have spread around the globe.  It all started, though, with prayer. As a young pastor, Wilkerson watched television in the evenings in order to know what the kids were watching. One day he was led by the Holy Spirit to stop watching television and instead dedicate his two hours of TV time to prayer. Little did he realize that that prayer time would result in God's leading him to minister to violent, hurting kids in the inner city, and eventually ministering to countless millions of teenagers over five decades of ministry.  On April 27, 2011, 79-year-old Wilkerson crossed over the center line and collided head-on with a tractor trailer while driving east on US Route 175 in Texas. He was pronounced dead on the scene.  Rev. Wilkerson's last blog post stated the following: "To those going through the valley and shadow of death, hear this word: Weeping will last through some dark, awful nights, and in that darkness you will soon hear the Father whisper, 'I am with you. I cannot tell you why right now, but one day it will all make sense. You will see it was all part of my plan. It was no accident.'"  Our hearts and prayers go out for the family and friends of David Wilkerson.  We are grateful for his life of love and his example of the work God can do in any one of us when we dedicate ourselves to Him.		2983

a modest sized library of texts and other training materials used as part of the curriculum in various colleges and universities.
In addition to the 4th and 5th editions of Linux Administration: A Beginner's Guide, He is also the author of a projects lab

by Prentice Hall.

where he usually hangs out and dreams up (albeit unsuccessfully) plans to take over the world. caffenix is possibly the world's
first (or only existing) brick and mortar store committed and dedicated to prompting and show-casing open source technologies
and culture.

IMPORTANT THINGS TO NOTE

Driving Directions
We ask that you please follow the directions that were provided in the wedding invitation. If you enter the address into a Google Maps/GPS system, it may misdirect you to the venue exit, which is about a mile away from the venue entrance. The directions are also listed below:

From San Francisco:

Hwy 280 South. Exit Hwy 85 South. Drive 4.1 miles and exit at Saratoga Avenue. Turn right onto Saratoga Avenue Drive 1.8 miles to downtown Saratoga. Turn left at light onto Hwy 9 / Saratoga - Los Gatos Road. Drive 1/3 mile and turn right onto Montalvo Road. Continue approximately 1 mile to Montalvo grounds.

From Oakland:

Hwy 880 South to Hwy 17 South. Take the Los Gatos, Saratoga, Hwy 9 Exit. Drive 3.5 miles. Turn left onto Montalvo Road. Continue approximately 1 mile to Montalvo grounds.

From San Jose:

Hwy 280 North to Hwy 17 South. Take the second Los Gatos Exit (Los Gatos, Saratoga, Hwy 9). Continue 3.5 miles. Turn left onto Montalvo Road. Continue 1 mile to Montalvo grounds.

From Santa Cruz:

Hwy 17 North. Take the Los Gatos, Saratoga, Hwy 9 Exit. Drive back over the freeway and continue 3.5 miles. Turn left onto Montalvo Road. Continue approximately 1 mile to Montalvo grounds.

Weather
It will be hot! The weather is projected to be 85-90 degrees on Saturday. Be sure to dress with the weather in mind.

Technology
There is no cell phone reception available on the Villa Montalvo grounds, so please plan accordingly.

To: mike adeniji, ADEJIMI ADENIJI, Taiwo-california Adeniji, Dotun Arifalo, Oluwaseun Adeniji (, benadeniji@gmail.com, Bukola Adeniji, Michael Adeniji, Shade-Bimpe Lawal, Ademola ADENIJI_Ademola - Gmail, (tutuadewole@gmail.com), Oscar Adeniji (, Wale Soyinka, FemiNC Adeniji, FEMI ADENIJI, Jumoke Adeniji olurinde, Jumoke Olurinde, Ken Adeniji
a_oluwatosin@yahoo.com
Dear All,
A very good day and thanks for all the concern that have been shown and perspectives shared on this challenge. God will make a way out of this mist and make sister Sola whole in Jesus name.
1. I spoke with sister Sola this Friday morning and she told me it was a heart challenge she's having.
2, I had a conversation with her doctor this afternoon to follow up on what sister Sola said. The doctor informed me it was blood cancer, and that it was the cancer in the blood that was responsible for the heart challenge. The doctor confirmed that an Oncologist had infact examined her and confirmed it was blood cancer.
3.Based on the above , I demanded for the specialist's report so as to get a possible second opinion  prior to commencement of treatment. Just to make assurance doubly sure.The doctor informed me that the specialist is gone to Abuja, as such I can only have the report when he's back in Ibadan , possibly next week.
4. Against the background of perceived 'smartness ' by Nigerian doctors, and the logical need to re validate the diagnosis, my take is that the initial report be checked.  As a first step, am supposed to connect with another specialist in Ibadan next week as government hospitals in Nigeria are on strike currently.
5. Sister Sola is in Ibadan. Yes, she is ill as confirmed by the doctor. I also visited her not too long ago.However, I do not think we all should be in panic mode. Rather, I suggest we take quick steps to get the right diagnosis and decide on which hospital/doctor is to treat her. On Friday, August 1, 2014 8:28 PM, mike adeniji <madeniji@hotmail.com> wrote:


 
Chronic lymphocytic leukemia is a type of cancer in which the bone marrow makes too
many lymphocytes (a type of white blood cell).
Chronic lymphocytic leukemia (also called CLL) is a blood and bone marrow disease that
usually gets worse slowly. CLL is one of the most common types of leukemia in adults.
It often occurs during or after middle age; it rarely occurs in children.
 
Chronic lymphocytic leukemia treatments can help control the disease
 
Lymphoma is the most common blood cancer. The two main forms of lymphoma are Hodgkin
lymphoma and non-Hodgkin lymphoma (NHL). Lymphoma occurs when cells of the immune
system called lymphocytes, a type of white blood cell, grow and multiply uncontrollably.
Cancerous lymphocytes can travel to many parts of the body, including the lymph nodes, spleen,
bone marrow, blood, or other organs, and form a mass called a tumor. The body has two main
types of lymphocytes that can develop into lymphomas: B-lymphocytes (B-cells) and
T-lymphocytes (T-cells).
 
Read More....
1) https://www.google.com/search?hl=en&gbv=2&q=lymphocytic+leukemia+survival+rate&revid=1435015151&sa=X&ei=cOfbU9WRIMPgsATr-IKoCQ&ved=0CHMQ1QIoAA

Creation (bara in Hebrew) in biblical terms is an act by which God brings some thing or some force into the universe. Only God can create. All other acts in Genesis are acts of making or forming things from already existing matter. According to all ancient commentary, the only creation that was physical was the opening sentence of the Bible, bringing our universe into being. The remaining two creations (Gen 1:21 and Gen. 1:27) were not physical. They were spiritual: the first, the nefesh, the soul of animal life, and the second, the neshamah, the soul of humankind. Hi Brett,

 

It was great to meet you (virtually) and I enjoyed our discussion.  I'm looking forward to figuring out how we can work together.

 

Here is a summary of a couple projects we are looking for help with:

Digital Primer (Hebrew Decoding) - (Developers)

We will be developing a new version of Shalom Uvrachah (one of our most popular digital products).  Shalom Urvachah Interactive was developed over 14 years ago and was our first full digital primer that teaches how to decode the Alef Bet.  Here is a link to see more the original version http://www.shalomuvrachah.com

The new digital Shalom Uvrachah will need to work with multiple ages from 2nd-3rd graders, 5th -6th graders, and adults.  We will be developing it to work on both modern web browsers and tablets.

 

Hebrew Prayer Series - (Project Manager and Developers)

Our new Hebrew prayer series core element will be learning prayers through music.  Video's and MP3's will have a major role in the digital piece.  It will be a blended classroom and digital experience.  The digital piece will need to work on all devices.  The prayers will be offered as separate modules, so educators can pick which ones they want to teach in any order.

Thanks,

	13989	2017-12-05 09:04:31.327	[sefaria-dev] Announcing METI's new Library of Judeo-Arabic Literature  Tod Robbins 	 3/10/14 This may be of interest to the list:  http://maxwellinstitute.byu.edu/announcing-library-of-judeo-arabic-literature/      On behalf of the Neal A. Maxwell Institute for Religious Scholarship, I am pleased to announce the addition of an important new series to our Middle Eastern Texts Initiative (METI). The series, to be called the Library of Judeo-Arabic Literature (LJAL), will publish works written by Jewish authors living within the Islamic world of the Middle Ages. At the invitation of James T. Robinson, a professor at the University of Chicago Divinity School, and David Sklare, of the Ben-Zvi Institute in Jerusalem, an international team of scholars have come together to edit, translate, and publish these texts in the same dual-language format as other METI publications like the Islamic Translation Series, and Eastern Christian Texts. The bilingual format makes primary texts and expert translations simultaneously available to experts, students, and general readers alike. Texts will be selected from across the entire range of genres represented in Judeo-Arabic literature, including philosophy, theology, Biblical interpretation, history, and many other genres.    --  Tod Robbins Digital Asset Manager, MLIS todrobbins.com | @todrobbins Post Discard By 	 me (Ken Adeniji change) Email updates to me 	Attach a file 	 Attach a file 		Edit subject 	Quote original 			   Post Discard 	Oren 	 9/19/14 Thank you Tod, The prospectus here says this about the corpus of literature in judeo-arabic, that they are:      Arabic texts composed by Jewish authors, usually written in Hebrew characters   This could indicate that not all were written in Hebrew characters and some were originally written in Arabic characters. Just wanted to point that out :) - show quoted text - 	Tod Robbins 	 9/20/14 Very cool! - show quoted text -      - show quoted text -     --      You received this message because you are subscribed to the Google Groups "Sefaria Developers" group. 	13991	2017-12-05 10:16:57.670	Sefaria Developers Fwd: Ben-Gurion researchers OCR Hebrew with niqud using Tesseract-OCR 1 post by 1 author 	Aharon Varady 	 12/22/13 Resending after bounce.  ---------- Forwarded message ---------- From: Aharon Varady aha...@opensiddur.org Date: Sun, Dec 22, 2013 at 8:52 PM Subject: Ben-Gurion researchers OCR Hebrew with niqud using Tesseract-OCR To: jewis...@googlegroups.com, sefar...@googlegroups.com, Open Siddur Technical Discussion List opensid...@googlegroups.com   A year ago, Shani Vered and Adi Oz documented how they trained Tesseract-OCR to read Hebrew with niqud.  You can check out their work here: http://www.cs.bgu.ac.il/~nlpproj/hocr and check out their own summary here: http://www.cs.bgu.ac.il/~elhadad/hocr/OCRWithNikud.pptx  This is exciting news and really, we need more folks duplicating their effort and sharing what they've learned so that we can get this sort of work out of the computer lab and into service.  We need help and we're looking for volunteers. This should be of interest to many of our projects.  If anyone tries this, please report back and let us know where you ran into problems or where you might need help.   Let's get moving on this.  Thanks.  Aharon   --  Aharon Varady Founding Director, Hierophant the Open Siddur Project http://opensiddur.org    --  Aharon Varady, M.C.P., M.A. J.Ed. Environmental Educator, Public Domain Advocate, Community Planner Writing | Research  Read my latest essay on the values underpinning an economy for sharing creativity in Torah. 	13992	2017-12-05 10:24:52.600	Hi all, 

Search is finally coming to Sefaria -- here's a preview of what will be released more broadly soon:

http://staging.sefaria.org/search?q=light

This is just the beginning of an ongoing project to make the best possible search experience across all Jewish texts. It's not very smart yet, but as with everything I'd like to get something usable out into the world so we can keep improving.

Please let me know if you find anything horribly broken that I should look into before a first release, or any other ideas you have or making this great. 

Some improvements that will be next on deck:

    Understanding of Hebrew Morphology (thanks to HebMorph)
    Ability to sort results chronologically
    Ability to see how many results appear in different categories, and to filter / drill down into categories like "Mishnah" vs "Midrash". 

Thanks,
Brett		8911

	15167	2019-07-16 20:11:28.860	https://www.songtime.com/about/our-staff/
Dr. John DeBrine

Founder and President Emeritus 

John DeBrine founded Songtime in 1963 and served as the president and host for 50 years before retiring in 2014.

John started his ministry in Youth For Christ and after joining the pastoral staff of Ruggles Street Baptist Church, founded Youth Time, a bi-weekly event for teens in the Greater Boston area. With a passion for religious broadcasting and nothing on the radio in Boston, John sought out to start a radio program that would play Christian music. Songtime was born and the original studio was set up in the Church's broom closet.

As the ministry grew, John stepped down from the pastorate to focus on Songtime and his itinerant preaching schedule. His ministry took him all over New England and the Northeast.

Today, John is happily retired and enjoying the ministry he still has with the various people who come by his house for his encouragement and witness. You can follow John on his FaceBook page here.		177
